we are using material ui 7. Grids look like this:
```tsx
<Grid container spacing={2}>
  <Grid size={8}>
    <Item>size=8</Item>
  </Grid>
  <Grid size={4}>
    <Item>size=4</Item>
  </Grid>
  <Grid size={4}>
    <Item>size=4</Item>
  </Grid>
  <Grid size={8}>
    <Item>size=8</Item>
  </Grid>
</Grid>
```
use the size, not xs or any other props.

To adjust sizes per screen size:
```tsx
  <Grid size={{
  xs: 8
  md: 12
  // etc...
  }}>
    <Item>size=8</Item>
  </Grid>
```
